Jul 14 2007 	Internet expensive and Concierges don't know the city well enough	The hotel regarding location, dining, room etc... is fantastic only 2 slight negatives after our stay of a week to look out for:1. INTERNET: If you don't have your computer and use the internet in the hotel's business centre it is very expensive at RMB2 a MINUTE. Cheaper to take walk 10min or take a taxi (RMB10) to an internet cafe nearby which costs RMB2 an HOUR. The internet places are open all night, have about 100 computers, all computers have headsets and microphones if you want to Skype someone and they even sell icecreams at RMB10 each (EUR0.10)!2. CONCIERGES: The various concierges at the hotel can sometimes not write down precise enough instructions for the taxi drivers which can leave you stuck at the requested location's nearby bus station instead of the requested shopping mall and they don't seem to know enough about Beijing. When we asked about a visit to the underground tunnels, the nearest supermarket etc... the concierges admitted they just didn't know or they advised us a place which we discovered in the end was further away. As a result this unfortunately left us sometimes with the need to find out thing for ourselves. Overall the hotel is wonderful and we will definitely return there again but in our opinion these 2 things could be improved and are something to look out for.	
